RELEASING FRIDAY AT 9AM pst. 
If I was being honest I had this design scheduled to release this week and then struggled if it was the right time because of the Memphis incident. Then last night happened and a Selma PD officer was killed. In my struggle to post I reached out to @ammoandgrace for some words of wisdom and realized now is the perfect time to release this. 
This has nothing to do with the bad we had to see in Memphis. This is for the good men and women who serve and protect. The Selma pd officer that was killed last night doing his job. And let’s be honest, the good far outweigh the bad. 5 bad cops will not weigh the good down. 5 bad cops will not define the thousands of good. The good will hold their heads up and rebuild the trust that was broken. The good will still go out and protect everyone after one of their own was just killed. 
Nobody hates a bad officer more than a good officer. 
The good need our support. Now is not the time to turn our backs. Now is the time we rally around the good and make them feel more loved and appreciated than ever. Backing the blue isn’t representative of the bad. It’s representative of the good. The REAL BLUE. The men and women who deserve our love and support all the time because they never waiver their service.  Now is the time to speak up and let those that we support and love, the good ones, and that will never waiver. 

This will be available in a cropped sweatshirt, full sweatshirt, long sleeve, and hoodie. In navy, black, black white wash, and navy white wash.

RELEASING FRIDAY 9am PST. ‼️PLEASE READ why this design is so special below‼️

We all NEED law enforcement. We need law and order, we need safety, we need protection. Spouses need their partners, kids need their parents, mothers and fathers need their children.. the list goes on. 

@megbertsmacros and I worked together on this design. Her husband is an officer at a department local to me. He was shot in the line of duty, serving a search warrant. Many surgeries later his leg ended up needing to be amputated to survive, among other injuries. She was day 62 in her first 75 hard challenge when the shooting happened. The 75 hard challenge stopped for her that day as my worse nightmare became her reality. If you follow her you know they are absolutely inspiring with how they have handled each part of it and how they changed a traumatic event into a lesson for everyone and have given so many people a new perspective. 

Megan decided to do 75 hard again but make it an even bigger challenge. She will be donating her own money and has been collecting donations as she checks in daily on her accomplishments of 75 hard. 

➡️ I decided to partner up with  with @megbertsmacros and donate 50% of the proceeds of this design along side Megan’s raised donations to our local C.O.P.S. Chapter. ⬅️

245 officers died in 2022. TWO HUNDRED FOURTY FIVE. C.O.P.S. (Concerns Of Police Survivors) is a non profit that steps in to support agencies and families of the officers that experience a line of duty death. This is something I will always stand behind. 

As a police wife myself I can tell you, I NEED my husband. My children NEED their father. 

Please consider making a purchase of this shirt on Friday. If you can’t purchase please share on your stories tagging me! Better yet, do both! Let’s get the word out and raise some money. This design will come in many shirt styles and in light grey and black as pictured. 

Due to this being a fundraiser it will not be part of the new release discount in order to try and raise as much money as possible.

245 officers were killed in the line of duty in 2022.
64 of those officers were shot. 

696 officers were killed in the line of duty in 2021.
64 of those officers were shot. 

My husband was shot in the line of duty in 2021 and I thank God EVERY single day that he wasn’t number 65. That the statistic we joined was “just” one of the 346 officers shot in 2021. 

We NEED officers. I NEED my husband. Hallie NEEDS her dad. 

I’m fundraising through #75Hard to donate money to an organization that supports families and agencies of fallen officers, and Tiffany has created this amazing shirt to donate alongside me! 💙 

Let’s see how much we can raise. We appreciate all the shares in case you know anyone else who would sport this in support!

So what started as a week of panic turned into so many designs circling my brain and not being able to limit my designing. This one is my favorite so far so I couldn’t wait to share it with you.
